Implemented the tank fill/drain controller policy in:

- `components/controller/controller.c`
- `components/controller/include/controller.h` (unchanged interface, verified against it)

Behavior now:
- boots pump off
- turns on below 30
- turns off above 80
- holds previous safe output in the mid band
- fails safe on malformed input or timeout
- treats `>1000 ms` since last valid sensor as timeout

Visible verification added:
- host-side controller policy tests for every checklist bullet
- firmware-level UART end-to-end probe for boot + low-to-high sequence

Checks run:
- `python3 tools/run_build.py`
- `python3 tools/run_self_tests.py`
- `python3 tools/run_eval.py` twice; latest submission recorded


